  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for families affected by COVID-19 third wave.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sri Lanka is experiencing a third wave of COVID-19 infection causing severe health, economic, and psychosocial impacts particularly for the most poor and vulnerable citizens. Rising levels of infection through May and June threatened to exceed the capacities of the health services,  and led to stringent restrictions on movement and association. As in previous lockdowns, those in informal employment or reliant on day labour were most severely impacted by loss of income and inability to afford food and essential items. Caritas Sri Lanka will respond through its 13 Diocesan Centres to provide essential food, non-food items including PPE, educational materials, and medical assistance, to a total of 5460 families.</narrative>
  </description>
